{
  "stem": "13063.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People came out sometimes when the-- when there were no Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First of all, whenever we came out from-- from-- from this house, we looked whether there are any Germans in the street.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If there were no Germans, people came out to greet-- greet each other, to exchange some impressions with one another, to exchange our information-- family information-- with one another, to voice hopes, perhaps, with other, and to [SIGHS] compare notes, compare notes.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But when the Germans were walking, there was-- the street was almost empty, because this spelled trouble when they were walking in the streets of ghetto.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were children in the ghetto, yes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were a lot of children in ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And some of them didn't know what was going on, so they were frolicking, the children.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But soon enough, in 19-- the end of 1941-- I think it was November-- the-- the transports started.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were-- the ghetto was surrounded by German-- by the-- by Germans in helmets, in steel helmets with machine guns.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they went with a list of people from-- from house to house, taking people out and towards the transport, towards the [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] railway station, where there were loaded in boxcars, in cattle cars, and transported out of Cracow.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody knew where.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Nobody knew the destination of those trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Within walking distance, about 2 miles, I would say, about 2 miles.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] By then, we didn't-- but you see, the Germans were so ingenious to try to cover their footprints, their murderous footprints, that they made somebody, before they are put to death, write a postcard-- we are OK, and we are going to work-- and send it to their dear ones.",
      "word_count": 54
    }
  ],
